00:03:40.130 --> 00:03:41.960
and I want to bring
it kind of full circle

00:03:41.960 --> 00:03:44.490
into the technology
of the heart and I'm

00:03:44.490 --> 00:03:47.700
going to ask you right now to
go with me to Konya, Turkey.

00:03:47.700 --> 00:03:50.560
How many people here have
actually been to Turkey?

00:03:50.560 --> 00:03:52.620
A few-- wow --of course
a Google audience,

00:03:52.620 --> 00:03:54.450
international audience.

00:03:54.450 --> 00:03:56.449
When I was-- many
years ago I was

00:03:56.449 --> 00:03:58.740
doing research for my first
novel, "The Virgin's Knot,"

00:03:58.740 --> 00:04:01.090
and I ended up in Konya,
Turkey doing research

00:04:01.090 --> 00:04:03.850
with a rug merchant
and his family

00:04:03.850 --> 00:04:06.886
and I ended up here at
the Whirling Dervish

00:04:06.886 --> 00:04:08.260
Lodge at the
[? Teki, ?] which is

00:04:08.260 --> 00:04:10.600
the monastery in Konya, Turkey.

00:04:10.600 --> 00:04:14.380
And I ended up at Rumi's tomb,
having absolutely no idea

00:04:14.380 --> 00:04:16.680
who this person Rumi was.

00:04:16.680 --> 00:04:20.885
And I see some glimmer in
the eyes of some of you.

00:04:20.885 --> 00:04:23.400
You can imagine what
